issue.title: Reduce lock contention in Thread.getAndClearInterrupt

repository.name: openj9-openjdk-jdk
repository.description: Extensions for OpenJDK for Eclipse OpenJ9

issue.body:
Lock contention in `Thread.getAndClearInterrupt` is reduced by
acquiring the lock only when the value of the `Thread.interrupted`
field is `true`.

Related: https://github.com/eclipse-openj9/openj9/issues/20414

timeline_data.body: Ran a 200x grinder: https://hyc-runtimes-jenkins.swg-devops.com/job/Grinder/46971. The failure couldn't be reproduced. Closing, please reopen if the failure is seen again.

issue.title: OpenJDK java/foreign/TestLinker crash fix

repository.name: openj9
repository.description: Eclipse OpenJ9: A Java Virtual Machine for OpenJDK that's optimized for small footprint, fast start-up, and high throughput.   Builds on Eclipse OMR (https://github.com/eclipse/omr) and combines with the Extensions for OpenJDK for OpenJ9 repo.

issue.body:
The changes reflect the fix for issue https://github.com/eclipse-openj9/openj9/issues/21017.

buildInternalNativeStackFrame before setting exception.
Added check for sequence layout of zero length.

Closes: https://github.com/eclipse-openj9/openj9/issues/21017
Signed-off-by: Nick Kamal <[nick.kamal@ibm.com](mailto:nick.kamal@ibm.com)>

timeline_data.body:
This failure is also observed with the RI. For more details, see https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8348578. The issue is believed to be related to the test case, specifically the code snippet below.

An initial suggestion was to increase the timeout before termination (`MAX_EXECUTOR_WAIT_SECONDS`), as the current timeout may be insufficient on slower machines. However, it was decided to gather more data before implementing a fix. The RI will eventually address the issue.

In the meantime, these failures can be ignored, and the test does not need to be excluded since the failure is highly intermittent. This issue does not block JDK 24 and can be deferred to the next release.

```
TestMappedHandshake.testHandshake(TestMappedHandshake.java:90):
       assertTrue(accessExecutor.awaitTermination(MAX_EXECUTOR_WAIT_SECONDS, TimeUnit.SECONDS));
```
@babsingh pls exclude the test anyway, there were 3 failures of this yesterday.
